<section class="section problem">
  <div class="container prose">
    <p class="eyebrow">The problem</p>
    <h2 class="h1 problem-headline">
      Your data is already everywhere. Nowhere is it actually useful.
    </h2>
    <div class="problem-body">
      <p>
        Your sleep ring knows your deep sleep minutes. Your workout app knows your heart rate zones.
        Your food log lives in a third place. Your doctor has your labs.
      </p>
      <p>
        None of them talk to each other. Every app shows you its own slice and leaves you to
        connect the dots.
      </p>
      <p class="problem-punch">That's not a coaching problem. That's a data problem.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem {
    background: var(--bg-primary);
  }

  .problem-headline {
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-8);
    max-width: 22ch;
  }

  .problem-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-5);
    font-size: var(--fs-body-lg);
    font-weight: var(--fw-light);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--lh-relaxed);
  }

  .problem-punch {
    font-size: var(--fs-h2);
    font-weight: var(--fw-regular);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    max-width: none;
  }
</style>
